Cameroon’s Main Opposition Elects Fru Ndi as Candidate for Oct. 9 Election

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-08-31T11:44:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/cameroon-s-main-opposition-elects-fru-ndi-as-candidate-for-oct-9-election.html
Cameroon ’s main opposition party,
the Social Democratic Front, elected John Fru Ndi as its
candidate for the country’s Oct. 9 presidential election, said
Joseph Banadzem, the head of the SDF’s parliamentary group.  “We have unanimously endorsed John Fru Ndi’s
candidature,” Banadzem said by phone today from Bamenda, in
northeastern Cameroon.  Parties have until Sept. 4 to submit candidates for the
vote.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde at 
 plukong@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
